oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Junior Order of United American Mechanics
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Photograph of members of the Junior Order of Mechanics prior to deployment for World War I. The man in the robe is the chaplain. The men are posed in front of the Jefferson City Post Office and an American flag.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Fraternal organizations; Soldiers; Post offices
